{"id":267,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":267,"title":"Chariot","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chariot","uri":"/scriptures/bd/chariot","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/chariot.t1","order":".000.715"},[".title","Chariot"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/chariot.p1","order":".000.716"},"A vehicle, generally used for purposes of war (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/14.7"},"Ex. 14:7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/17.18"},"Josh. 17:18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/1.19"},"Judg. 1:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/4.3"},"4:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/13.5"},"1 Sam. 13:5"],"). Up to the time of David the Israelites had few chariots (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/8.11-12"},"1 Sam. 8:11–12"],"); in later times a regular force was maintained (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.4"},"2 Sam. 8:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/10.26"},"1 Kgs. 10:26"],"). The armies that fought against Israel also had chariots, such as the Syrians (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.4"},"2 Sam. 8:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/8.21"},"2 Kgs. 8:21"],"), the Assyrians (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/19.23"},"2 Kgs. 19:23"],"), and the Persians (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/22.6-7"},"Isa. 22:6–7"],"). The Israelite fighting chariot was probably after the Egyptian model, the plan of which is known from Egyptian paintings and reliefs still in existence."]]],"refs":null}
